metadata.name: Herald of the Sun
metadata.description:
"Herald of the Sun" portrays two figures gracefully floating in the sky, embodying a reinterpretation of Greek mythology. The first figure represents Helios, the God of the Sun. Seated upon a cloud, Helios holds the radiant Sun, whose rays illuminate the world with life, enlightenment, and spiritual illumination.

Beside Helios, we find Phosphorus, known as the bringer of light and the Herald of the Sun. Phosphorus gazes upon their mentor, entrusted with the task of spreading the light to every corner of the world. In their yearning for growth, Phosphorus symbolizes the human pursuit of wisdom and the desire to draw closer to the truth.

Together, Helios and Phosphorus depict the interplay between life's essence and the eternal quest for growth and transcendence. "Herald of the Sun" speaks to our innate longing for spiritual awakening and the unwavering pursuit of profound meaning in our lives.
